	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />First thing to check out would be the voltage regulator, probably looking like this: <a href="http://www.pw-electronics.co.uk/ICs%20and%20Semi/ICs%20and%20Semi%20Photos/MC7805CT.jpg" class="postlink">http://www.pw-electronics.co.uk/ICs%20and%20Semi/ICs%20and%20Semi%20Photos/MC7805CT.jpg</a>
<br />
<br />I've had a couple devices fried by power input, that worked after replacing the voltage regulator (and an exploded capacitor in one case).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


