	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yep, 7809 would be my guess also.  If you have a multimeter (or DC voltmeter) it would be easy to test.  Power it on, connect ground to the middle pin, then with the other probe you should see around 12V (or anything really) on the first pin and (if it's working) 9V on the 3rd pin (the output).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


